<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="167" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/193:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-09T19:00:00-04:00">August 9, 1929—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>263. Your 688, August 8, 7 p.m. The Department feels that the sending of
                            such a note at this time would only further cloud the situation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>